title._content: Large group of IWW members at picnic, Seattle, Washington, July 20, 1919

description._content: General Notes: A banner hanging above the group with a picture of a man in jail says: "[Remember! We're in For You. Will you out there remember us? Liberty Bonds, War Saving Stamps and cash from $5.00 and up accepted here as loan for bail of Class War Prisoners--All Together-All for One and One For All.]" Photographer: Unknown Subjects (LCSH): Industrial Workers of the World -- History. Industrial Workers of the World.
